@Node Utilisation "First Use"
@{b}For a good start@{ub}


The first time, it's necessary to configure De-Archiveur with the
Workbench menu icon->information for the fonts to use, Where you
want the place of the Appicon of De-Archiveur, the coordinate of the
window, the hotkey and popkey, ....


After, launch it whith double-clicking in his icon. A window with
all the possibility of De-Archiveur appared. You MUST configure the
path of each archiveurs you have, the drawer for the documentations....


You can iconify De-Archiveur with the gadget in the left high of the
principal window. Double-click in the Appicon show you again the GUI.


De-Archiveur is a commodity and is completely checked with Exchange or
similar clone of the workbench (like CX). Exchange allows you to
switch off, quitting, show GUI of De-Archiveur, etc....


In an Appicon form, De-Archiveur allows you to pack or unpack directly
with dropping the archive or the drawer you want and enter the name you
want with the prefix of the archiver you neeed.
@Endnode

@Node Fenetre principale "The principal window"

@{b}The principal window of De-Archiveur@{ub}

                  Blitz De-Archiveur

             @{"  AUTO    " LINK AUTO}     @{" SETTINGS " LINK preference}
             @{"  UNPACK  " LINK DECRUNCH}     @{"   PACK   " LINK CRUNCH}
             @{"  TEST    " LINK TEST}     @{"   ABOUT  " LINK A PROPOS}

             @{" HELP " LINK HELP}    @{" QUIT " LINK QUITTER}    @{" DOC " LINK DOC}
             
@Endnode

@Node auto "Automatic mode"

Allow  De-Archiveur  to  choose  atomatically the archiver you need or
select the archivers you use the most often.

@Endnode 

@Node preference "Preferences window"

Give an access to the config window of De-Archiveur.

keyboard shortcut: AMIGA + P
@Endnode 

@Node decrunch "decrunch a file"

Unpack  one  or more file with a file-requester in the drawer you have
choosen in the prefs window.

keyboard shortcut: AMIGA + D
@Endnode 

@Node crunch "crunch a file"

Crunch  one or more file and before De-Archiveur ask you which name it
must use for the archive (a default name is also possible).

keyboard shortcut: AMIGA + C
@Endnode 
@Node test "test a file"

Test if a file is good.

keyboard shortcut: AMIGA + T
@Endnode 

@Node a propos "About this program"

The  about  requester show you informations about De-Archiveur and his
authors.

keyboard shortcut: AMIGA + A
@Endnode 
@Node help "Small help for differents options"

This  button  give  you  a  small  help  for the differents fonctions.
Simply  click  this button and after click the button you want to know
the  fonctions.  A small help appared under the window of the options.
To switch off the small help, simply click in the help button.

@EndNode

@Node doc "Using the documentation in  AmigaGuide"

This  documentation  is  available  directly  in De-Archiveur.  Simply
click  in  the  doc  button  and  have the good path of the Amigaguide
Documentation.

keyboard shortcut:  AMIGA + H
@Endnode 

@Node quitter "quit this program"

Quit De-Archiveur

keyboard shortcut: AMIGA + Q
@Endnode 

@Node Preferences "Program preferences"

@{b} Preferences window  @{ub}

	     @{" Settings archiveurs " LINK preferences-xxx}

	@{" Path Source      " LINK source}   @{" Cmd unpacker " LINK cmd-decompactage}
	@{" Path Destination " LINK Destination}   @{" Cmd packer   " LINK Cmd-compactage}
	@{" Use packer       " LINK compacteur}   @{" Cmd test     " LINK Cmd-listing}
	@{" Use unpacker     " LINK decompacteur}   @{" Cmd shell    " LINK Cmd-shell}
	@{" DMS Method       " LINK DMS-Methode}   @{" close shell  " LINK temps-du-shell}

        @{" Save settings " LINK sauver-preferences}   @{" Use " LINK Utiliser}    @{" Quit " LINK partir}

Explanations for each options are the same for all the archivers.

@endnode

@Node Preferences-xxx  "Settings for archivers"

With  this  button,  you  can  choose  the archiver you want to change
parameters available with De-Archiver.
@EndNode

@Node Source "Path source"

The path you habitually use where your archived programs are stocking.

@EndNode
 
@Node Cmd-compactage "commands for packing"

Commands necessary for packing an archive.   

@EndNode

@Node Destination "Path destination"

The path you habitually use to stocking your archived programs.

@EndNode

@Node Cmd-decompactage "Cmd unpacker"

Commands necessary for unpacking an archive.
@EndNode

@Node Compacteur "Use packer"

The path where your packers are.
@EndNode

@Node Cmd-listing "Cmd test"

Commands necessary for testing or listing an archive.
@EndNode

@Node Decompacteur "Use unpacker"

The path where your unpackers are (for example unzip).
@EndNode

@Node Cmd-shell "Cmd shell"

Commands necessary for creating a shell window.

ex: Newcli window con:0/11/640/100/De-Archiveur/close.

@EndNode
   
@Node Temps-du-shell "Close shell"

You  can  choose  the time you want to see the shell window containing
the   informations  of  the  archive  after  a  packing  or  unpacking
operation.

It's impossible to quit the window before the time.

Don't put a too long time.
@EndNode

@Node DMS-Methode " DMS Method"

You can choose the method you want to use DMS.

@EndNode

@Node Sauver-preferences "save settings"

Save settings.

@EndNode
     
@Node Utiliser "Use the new settings"

Only use the new settings.

@EndNode
   
@Node partir "Quit the settings"

Quit the program.

@EndNode

@Node Tooltypes "Tooltypes"
@{b}The Tooltypes are:@{ub}

@{b}DONOTWAIT@{ub}

@{b}POPUP=YES or NO@{ub}

Use De-Archiveur with his GUI or in an appicon mode.

@{b}HIDE= YES or NO@{ub}

Hide or not De-Archiveur for a control by Exchange.

@{b}CX_POPKEY=Ctrl m@{ub}

Keyboard shortcut to call De-Archiveur.

@{b}CX_HOTKEY=Ctrl c@{ub}

Keyboard shortcut to hide De-Archiveur.

@{b}ICONY@{ub}

Coordinate of the appicon in Y.

@{b}ICONX@{ub}

Coordinate of the appicon in X.

@{b}WINDOWX=Nbre@{ub}

Coordinate X for the principal window of De-Archiveur.

@{b}WINDOWY=Nbre@{ub}

Coordinate Y for the principal window of De-Archiveur.

@{b}WINDOWPREFX=Nbre@{ub}

Coordinate X for the preferences window of De-Archiveur.

@{b}WINDOWPREFY=Nbre@{ub}

Coordinate Y for the preferences window of De-Archiveur.

@{b}VIEWER-GUIDE=nom@{ub}

Path and name of the viewer of guide.

@{b}PATH=nom @{ub}

Preferences saving.

@{b}FONT-MENU=topaz.font@{ub}

Name of the fonts using in the menus.

@{b}TAILLEFONT-MENU=Nbre@{ub}

Height of the fonts using in the menus.

@{b}FONT-BOUTONS=xhelvetica.font@{ub}

Name of the fonts using in the buttons.

@{b}TAILLEFONT-BOUTONS=Nbre@{ub}

Height of the fonts using in the buttons.

@{b}CHEMIN-DOC=chemin@{ub}

Path for the documentation.
@Endnode
